THE GAME
--------

  'Ang' is a Workbench game where you have to move 'angles'
(represented by 90 degrees angle shaped tiles), so they form
2 by 2 tiles square patterns. The angles can move diagonally
toward the direction they are pointing... To ease (or maybe
complicate?) matters, all angles can 'wrap around' the game
board's edge so they continue to move on the opposite side.

  As angles are moved, if an angle moves toward another, both
angles will 'exchange' their positions... unless the other angle
is of the same shape, meaning that it is pointing in the same
direction.

  Every time you move an angle and it does not complete a square
shape, a new angle will randomly appear on the game board... so
beware that the game board does not get filled up completely, as
that would end the game.

  Try as much as possible to make square shapes using 3 or 4
angles of the same colour, as that will give you more points...

  Have fun!

